# StellerNet — Exoplanet Detection with Deep Learning

> Detecting exoplanet transits in Kepler space telescope light curves using a 1D Convolutional Neural Network.

---

## Overview

When a planet passes in front of a star, it causes a tiny dip in the star's brightness. This project trains a CNN to automatically detect these **transit signals** from NASA's Kepler mission data — a classic needle-in-a-haystack problem with extreme class imbalance (135:1 ratio).

