## Key Decisions

**Why per-star normalisation?**
Raw Kepler flux values differ vastly between stars. Normalising each star against itself (`axis=1`) preserves the transit dip shape while removing absolute scale differences.

**Why 10% SMOTE instead of full balance?**
Full SMOTE (100% balance) gave recall 1.00 but precision 0.01 — the model memorised synthetic patterns. At 10%, it learned real transit shapes: precision and recall both reached 0.714.

**Why threshold 0.7?**
Standard 0.5 threshold flagged too many false alarms. At 0.7 the model is selective — only confident predictions are classified as planets.

